Oof, leaving the comfy, warm bed for this AM practice...STRUGGLE.  

One of the mantras I've started this week: One Thing at a Time. Just taking whatever is in front of me and immersing myself in it as much as possible. My thoughts might still run a bit untamed and Lord knows I still get distracted (i have been toggling between writing this and dance party-ing), but still, it's a gentle reminder to return to the moment. 

& I also think that One Thing At a Time helps to... DO things more effectively. Multi-tasking/attention-splitting is a manifestation of the fear that I'm not using my time as productively as I could, so then, it ends up just trying to do one thing, having that nebulous fear that I'm not Doing the Right Thing, then jumping over to another thing...which is, uh...not super-productive. But if I can just accept and savor what is - that this is the thing I'm doing right now and I'll enjoy it - then I can let one moment flow into the next and expand both the ACTUAL time I have and my experience of time, as well. 
So, namaste all! May you step in the flow of life. May your presence be your power, and may you savor every moment for the precious, fleeting, and complete thing that it is, in and of itself :)
